{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-09T12:43:23Z", "url": "https://www.pcworld.com/article/2666388/acer-excellent-productivity-laptop-with-touchscreen-is-300-off.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-09T12:43:23Z", "content": "Skip to contentType your search and hit enter\r\nWhen you purchase through links in our articles, we may earn a small commission. This doesn't affect our editorial independence\r\n.\r\nA daily driver laptoâ€¦ [+2253 chars]", "title": "Acerâ€™s excellent productivity laptop with touchscreen is $300 off", "fullContent": "A daily driver laptop is what most of us need for work and leisure, and we always want to grab one thatâ€™s affordable yet powerful. If youâ€™re in the market for such a laptop, hereâ€™s a sweet deal to pounce on: Acerâ€™s Swift Go 14 laptop is only $649 at B&H. Thatâ€™s a massive $300 off!\n\nWith an Intel Core Ultra 7 155H processor, a decent 16GB of LPDDR5X RAM, and 512GB of SSD storage, this is a fast and capable machine that can handle all things work-related, plus it can stream high-res video and even do some light gaming. Donâ€™t push it too hard because it doesnâ€™t have a dedicated graphics card, but the integrated Intel Arc graphics are good enough if youâ€™re willing to compromise on settings.\n\nWhile the 14-inch screen may not seem very large, it is a touchscreen. Thatâ€™s great for convenient finger navigation, which comes in handy for reading PDFs, browsing the web, etc. And it all looks crisp with its 1920Ã—1200 resolution, but the 60Hz refresh rate leaves something to be desiredâ€”itâ€™s merely adequate for light gaming.\n\nThe Acer Swift Go 14 comes with two Thunderbolt 4 ports, which isnâ€™t too common on laptops in this price range. These are super-fast USB-C ports that can transfer files in a flash and handle video display for external monitors. You also get two USB-A 3.2 ports, a full-sized HDMI 2.1 port, a headset jack, and a microSD card slot. Thatâ€™s a pretty darn good offering for a productivity laptop.\n\nWe tested the Acer Swift Go 14 and had nothing but praise for it: â€œItâ€™s true that the Swift Go 14 isnâ€™t the most high-end luxurious model you can buy, but itâ€™s not trying to be either. Itâ€™s a travel workhorse. Strong enough to get you through everyday tasks, whether thatâ€™s Office apps or checking email, and light enough not to weigh you down.â€\n\nAt $649, the Acer Swift Go 14 is an absolute bargain and you should definitely add it to your cart sooner rather than later because awesome deals like this tend to come and go fast.\n\nSave $300 on this travel workhorse laptop for daily productivity\n\nFor more laptop buying advice see our articles on all the best laptop deals and the best laptops weâ€™ve tested."}
